{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef\/takeRef()"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindinggroupref\/takeref()"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"takeRef()","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","extendedModule":"GLibObject","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject15BindingGroupRefV","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","text":"ObjectRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In other words, this function will convert a floating reference (if","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"present) into a full reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically you want to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this function is helpful.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"GObject. We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"where the object that is being returned already exists)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At the same time, the API style of some popular GObject-based"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"libraries (such as Gtk) make it likely that for newly-created GObject"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instances, the user can be saved some typing if they are allowed to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"return a floating reference.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them. The caller will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that has been converted to a full reference.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_ref_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" running at the same time in another thread on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"text":" runs first then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference. If "},{"code":"g_object_take_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" runs first then the result will be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"additional reference on top of that one is added. It is best to avoid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this situation."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/BindingGroupRef/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations","type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindinggroupref\/objectprotocol-implementations","kind":"article"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"role":"symbol","title":"ObjectRef"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","abstract":[],"title":"GLibObject","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/BindingGroupRef/takeRef()":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef\/takeRef()","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"takeRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindinggroupref\/takeref()","title":"takeRef()"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/BindingGroupRef":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"BindingGroupRef"}],"title":"BindingGroupRef","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"BindingGroupRef"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"code":"GBindingGroup","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used to bind multiple properties"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from an object collectively.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindinggroupref"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Object":{"title":"Object","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/object","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"role":"symbol"}}}